data.title: Wiz Khalifa, Juicy J, One Direction's Liam Payne Team Up on "You": Listen
data.meta_description: Also check out "Two Blunts (420)," a collaboration between Wiz and the Game
data.text:
Wiz Khalifa and Juicy J have reportedly been working on a new mixtape with 808 Mafia producer TM88 for a new mixtape. Today, a single called "You" has surfaced, and it features vocals from One Direction's Liam Payne. It's reportedly one of five songs Payne recorded with the two rappers. Listen below via TMZ, and check out a tracklist for the upcoming mixtape shared by TM88. Also below, find the Game and Khalifa's special 4/20 collaboration "Two Blunts (420)." Update (4/20, 8:15 p.m. EST): Payne has called the track a leak of a "scratch demo" in a series of tweets:

Wiz and Juicy J have worked together numerous times. Juicy J is on Wiz's Taylor Gang label. He appeared on "iSay" from Wiz's latest album Khalifa. He and TM88 also co-produced the single "Bake Sale." Earlier this month, Wiz and J were both featured on Domo Genesis' "Go (Gas)," and in 2014, they teamed up for the Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles song "Shell Shocked."
